
# Omega IPTV Rust Release Guide

## Overview

Omega IPTV Rust is a production-grade Rust IPTV pipeline.

It supports:

- Zee5 channel fetching
- JioTV channel fetching
- IPTV-org M3U parsing
- SQLite persistence
- Jio to IPTV-org matching
- Review generation
- Unified JSON export
- M3U playlist generation
- Jio EPG fetching
- XMLTV generation
- XMLTV gzip generation
- Public artifact publishing for GitHub Pages

---

## Main Safe Build Command

Use this on local VM:

```bash
CARGO_BUILD_JOBS=1 cargo run -p omega-cli -- build --epg-limit 20 --start-offset 0 --end-offset 1
```bash
### This runs:
```plain text
Fetch Zee5
Fetch Jio
Parse IPTV-org
Match channels
Export JSON
Generate M3U
Fetch limited Jio EPG
Generate XMLTV
Publish public files
Validate outputs
```

## Fast Build Without EPG
```bash 
CARGO_BUILD_JOBS=1 cargo run -p omega-cli -- build --skip-epgShow
```

## Full EPG Build
```Shell
CARGO_BUILD_JOBS=1 cargo run -p omega-cli -- build --start-offset 0 --end-offset 5Show
```

## Health Check
```Shell
CARGO_BUILD_JOBS=1 cargo run -p omega-cli -- doctorShow
```

## Download IPTV-org India M3U
```Shellcurl -L -o in.m3u https://raw.githubusercontent.com/iptv-org/iptv/refs/heads/master/streams/in.m3uShow more lines

Manual Pipeline Commands
Fetch Providers
ShellCARGO_BUILD_JOBS=1 cargo run -p omega-cli -- fetch all --persistShow more lines
Parse IPTV-org
ShellCARGO_BUILD_JOBS=1 cargo run -p omega-cli -- parse iptv-org --input in.m3u --persist`Show more lines
Match Channels
ShellCARGO_BUILD_JOBS=1 cargo run -p omega-cli -- matchShow more lines
Export JSON
ShellCARGO_BUILD_JOBS=1 cargo run -p omega-cli -- export allShow more lines
Generate Playlist
ShellCARGO_BUILD_JOBS=1 cargo run -p omega-cli -- playlistShow more lines
Fetch Test Jio EPG
ShellCARGO_BUILD_JOBS=1 cargo run -p omega-cli -- epg jio --limit 20 --start-offset 0 --end-offset 1 --persist``Show more lines
Generate XMLTV
ShellCARGO_BUILD_JOBS=1 cargo run -p omega-cli -- xmltvShow more lines
Publish Output
ShellCARGO_BUILD_JOBS=1 cargo run -p omega-cli -- publishShow more lines

